<Window x:Class="SimTools.BuyWarning"
        xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
        xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
        xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
        xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
        mc:Ignorable="d"
        Title="SimTools - Important Warning"
        Height="612" Width="530"
        WindowStyle="None" AllowsTransparency="True"
        WindowStartupLocation="CenterOwner"
        ResizeMode="NoResize">

    <Window.Background>
        <ImageBrush ImageSource="/Images/TS3_Box2.png"/>
    </Window.Background>

    <Grid>

        <!-- Warning summary — red bold italic -->
        <TextBlock x:Name="Text1" HorizontalAlignment="Left" Margin="32,40,0,0"
                   TextWrapping="Wrap" VerticalAlignment="Top"
                   Width="465" Height="73"
                   Foreground="Red" FontWeight="Bold" FontStyle="Italic"
                   FontFamily="Tahoma" FontSize="11"
                   Text="With partner sites, It is recommended to buy direct from the partner whenever possible and avoid third-party sellers on their sites, as some of these sellers have used illegitimate means (Stolen CC, Chargebacks) to purchase the keys and the keys could be revoked later. Purchasing direct from EA or Steam is highly recommended. The higher the prices, the more likely the deal is legitimate."/>

        <!-- Detailed body -->
        <TextBlock x:Name="Text2" HorizontalAlignment="Center" Margin="0,112,0,0"
                   TextWrapping="Wrap" VerticalAlignment="Top"
                   Width="465" Height="412"
                   FontFamily="Tahoma" FontSize="10" FontWeight="Bold">
            <Run Text="Many of these third party sites are legitimate in scope, and often times have good deals and trustworthy merchants. However, there is sometimes a bad apple in the batch. Be wary of low prices and deals that are too good to be true, they usually are."/>
            <LineBreak/><Run/><LineBreak/>
            <Run Text="Why buying the CHEAPEST option can hurt you:"/>
            <LineBreak/>
            <Run Text="• You're far more likely to encounter a merchant who has used illegitimate means to procure the key in question, this can range from stealing credit card information and using it to purchase the key, wherein the original owner eventually catches on and requests a chargeback for the amount. The game publisher will then have to pay that back to the bank, will then backtrack the transaction that the game key is linked to and revoke said game key."/>
            <LineBreak/>
            <Run Text="• Second to the above, the merchant themselves will later (and intentionally) issue a chargeback on their own card they used to make a quick buck off the illegitimate transaction. Like above, publisher will backtrack and revoke again."/>
            <LineBreak/>
            <Run Text="• Even if you're not in the wrong, each time a key is revoked for a chargeback transaction, there is always the potential for a black mark on your gaming account. Gain enough of these, and the publisher retains the right to restrict your access to the platform, or deny it altogether."/>
            <LineBreak/><Run/><LineBreak/>
            <Run Text="If you are going to buy from third party vendors, please follow these suggestions:"/>
            <LineBreak/>
            <Run Text="• Try to buy DIRECTLY from the partner whenever possible and not from the third-party merchants on their platform."/>
            <LineBreak/>
            <Run Text="• Look for prices relative to what you would expect. If a Sims 3 expansion typically costs $19.99 at any given time, then a deal that is $7-$10 is probably your best bet. Anything lower than that carries a potential risk."/>
            <LineBreak/>
            <Run Text="• Examine the merchants reviews and transaction history. Do they sell a lot of that title, are most people satisfied, pay close attention to how long between the customer buying the item and the time they left the review. The longer the better."/>
            <LineBreak/><Run/><LineBreak/>
            <Run Text="If any of the key points above give you pause, then by all means, stick to buying through official channels or sites you feel you can trust. Often times, Sims 3 will go on sale on Steam for 50% - 75% off (10.00 - 5.00 per expansion), these are the best times to buy extra expansions or stuff packs, and when done so through steam they can typically be registered on EA App as well."/>
        </TextBlock>

        <!-- Close button -->
        <Button x:Name="CloseButton"
                Content="Close"
                HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Bottom"
                Margin="456,0,0,22"
                Width="24" Height="37"
                FontFamily="Tahoma" FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="11"
                BorderBrush="{x:Null}"
                Click="CloseButton_Click" Foreground="{x:Null}" Background="{x:Null}" Opacity="0"/>

    </Grid>
</Window>
